   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="bibliography" subtype="edition">
            <ab>First published, with French translation, in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:huber-1911"/>: <biblScope>261</biblScope></bibl>; whence, with English translation, in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:majumdar-1927"/>: <biblScope>15</biblScope></bibl>, whence <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:golzio-2004"/>: <biblScope>10</biblScope>.</bibl> Re-edited from the inked EFEO estampages and available photos, with new translation, in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:ECIC-V"/>: <biblScope><seg type="check">forthcoming</seg></biblScope></bibl>, whence the present edition.</ab>
         </div>  
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="sa-Latn-x-CI" xml:space="preserve" rend="break-verse-lines">
            <lg met="Āryā">
            <l><lb n="1"/>śrīcampeśvaravijayī <unclear>m</unclear>ahāmatiś śrī<lb n="2" break="no"/>prakāśadharmmeti</l> 
            <l>sthāpitavān amareśa<unclear>ṃ</unclear> mahā<gap reason="illegible" extent="4-5" unit="character"></gap></l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <ab>
               <app loc="a">
                  <lem>śrīcampeśvara°</lem>
                  <rdg resp="Huber">śrī campeśvaro</rdg>
               </app>
               <app loc="b">
                  <lem><unclear>m</unclear>ahāmatiś śrī°</lem>
                  <rdg resp="Huber">mahīpati ... śrī</rdg>
               </app> 
               <app loc="b">
                  <lem>amareśa<unclear>ṃ</unclear> mahā<gap reason="illegible" extent="4-5" unit="character"></gap></lem>
                  <rdg resp="Huber">amareśam iha ...</rdg>
               </app> 
            </ab>
         </div>         
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <p>The illustrious conqueror, king of Campā, of great wisdom, called Śrī Prakāśadharman, has established Amareśa, the great...</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>L'illustre conquérant, roi du Campā, de grande sagesse, appelé Śrī Prakāśadharman, a établi Amareśa, le grand ...</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>It was not recognized by Huber that the inscription is metrical. Insufficient materials are at our disposal at this time to establish the whole text, but what is clear is that it concerns the erection of Amareśa, no doubt a <foreign>liṅga</foreign> of Śiva. Cf. <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:bisschop-2006"/>: <biblScope>33 with n. 79</biblScope>.</bibl></p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography" subtype="secondary">
            <listBibl>
               <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:parmentier-1918"/>: <biblScope>439 and 587</biblScope>.</bibl>
            </listBibl>
         </div>
      </body>
